29/06/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano conducted a series of key meeting with officials at the NATO summit in Istanbul.
On Monday (28 June), Nano met with his Romanian counterpart, Adrian Nastase, who gave strong assurances that his country -- which is now a NATO member -- would focus on helping Albania, Macedonia and Croatia gain entry.
A similar message was communicated by Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg and by Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi, who noted Albania's contributions to the fight against terrorism.
(ATA - 28/06/04)
